<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,970,1338,1401]" box="[151,311,1375,1401]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<figureCitation box="[151,311,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Figs. 239–240</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1446,1472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Description.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[404,505,1447,1473]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">holotype</typeStatus>
, male, with the labels “ 
<quantity box="[757,829,1447,1473]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" unit="km" value="40.0">40 km</quantity>
South of Zhana-Arka St.[Railway Station], Karaganda Obl[ast] [
<collectingCountry box="[257,397,1482,1509]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
]. 16.IX.[19]60. Emelyanov” (handwritten, in Russian, our comments in square brackets) and “ 
<typeStatus box="[161,281,1519,1545]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Holotypus</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Emelyanov" authorityName="Emelyanov" box="[287,620,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seriphidii">
<emphasis box="[287,483,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Agallia seriphidii</emphasis>
Emelyanov
</taxonomicName>
” (on red paper, first word printed, species name and author handwritten), deposited in Zoological Institute of Russian Academy of Sciences, St. Petersburg was investigated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
Penis in side view with serrated ventral crest in basal half and slightly concave dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1359,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 239</figureCitation>
). Male anal collar appendage narrow, bent upwards, with pointed tip (
<figureCitation box="[850,950,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
The genital block was dissected into separate parts; the part that we consider to be male anal collar appendage is shown on 
<figureCitation box="[299,398,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
. The shape of anal collar appendage on the drawing in the original description is different although the shape of the penis is exactly the same, as on 
<figureCitation box="[800,897,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 239</figureCitation>
. Drawings of this species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[1226,1401,1735,1761]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" refId="ref13797" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (1971) Cicadinea of Kazakhstan. Keys for identification of species. &quot; Nauka &quot; Publ., Alma-Ata, 211 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1971">Mityaev (1971)</bibRefCitation>
do not clarify the situation, since they are reproduced from the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="271" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1806,1832]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Biology.</emphasis>
On 
<taxonomicName box="[343,452,1807,1833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,452,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subg. 
<emphasis box="[536,673,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Seriphidium</emphasis>
). Hibernates at the egg stage and reaches 3 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1158,1187,1806,1833]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">rd–</superScript>
4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1200,1213,1806,1820]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">th</superScript>
instar by the end of June. In July–August, when host plants wither, the development of nymphs temporarily stops and resumes in the end of August. Adult specimens emerge in September (Emelyanov, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" box="[199,495,1914,1941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1914,1940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Calling signal.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
